  "prompt": "What is the syllabus of amcat?",
  "response": "AMCAT (Aspiring Minds Computer Adaptive Test) is a computer-based employability skills test that assesses a candidate's job readiness. While the exact syllabus can vary slightly depending on the specific job role or industry, here's a general overview of the typical AMCAT syllabus:\n\n1. Quantitative Ability:\n- Basic Mathematics\n- Arithmetic\n- Algebra\n- Geometry\n- Data Interpretation\n- Percentages\n- Ratios and Proportions\n- Time and Work\n- Speed, Distance, and Time\n\n2. Logical Reasoning:\n- Puzzles\n- Seating Arrangements\n- Blood Relations\n- Series Completion\n- Coding-Decoding\n- Data Sufficiency\n- Syllogisms\n- Problem-Solving\n\n3. Verbal Ability:\n- Reading Comprehension\n- Grammar\n- Sentence Correction\n- Vocabulary\n- Antonyms and Synonyms\n- Idioms and Phrases\n- Para Jumbles\n- Error Spotting\n\n4. Domain-Specific Sections (varies by job role):\n- Computer Programming\n- Software Engineering\n- Mechanical Engineering\n- Electrical Engineering\n- Electronics\n- Aptitude for specific industries\n\n5. Communication Skills Assessment\n\n6. Optional Sections (depending on the specific test):\n- English Communication\n- Technical Skills\n\nNote: The exact content and weightage of sections may vary based on the specific job role and industry requirements.",
